Subject: Re: [T2] Battery tray welding question

If he is very good with thin rod...  Body metal is very thin for welding
prone to easy burn-through as well as deformation (basically a real PITA!).
Much nicer to use a thin wire MIG setup (gas not flux-cored).

YMMV
Bill
